Class SessionConnectionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.proz.checkers.server.infrastructure.SessionConnectionController

    • Method Detail

      • addClient

        public void addClient(SocketChannel client,
                      int client_number)
               throws IOException
        Registers client channel. Registered channels are to be used to exchange messages with clients
        Parameters:
        client - Accepted channel to be registered in private selector
        client_number - client ID
        Throws:
        IOException - when the channel passed cannot be registered to the selector

      • getRequest

        public Request getRequest()
                   throws IOException
        Method performs receiving of data if any data is to be read. Receiving no data from clients means that a connection has been closed, then a Stop request is returned.
        Returns:
        polymorphic Request received from a client
        Throws:
        IOException - when receiving messages goes wrong
        See Also:
        Request

      • sendResponse

        public void sendResponse(Response response)
                  throws IOException
        Serializes polymorphic Response to JSON format String and writes it to a channel depending on response player ID field
        Parameters:
        response - polymorphic response that is sent to client
        Throws:
        IOException - when writing to a closed channel
